---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../components/sections/CTA.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="API"
  description="Cinturon360 is being designed as an API-first platform. Discover how TMCs and technology partners can integrate with the platform."
>
  <div class="pt-24 pb-16" style="background: var(--c360-dark);">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl text-center">
      <span class="section-badge section-badge-primary mb-4">API Platform</span>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
        Build on top of <span style="color: var(--c360-primary);">Cinturon</span><span style="color: var(--c360-accent);">360</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed" style="color: rgba(248,250,252,0.55);">
        Cinturon360 is being designed as more than a user interface. It is being built as a travel governance and visibility platform that TMCs and partners can connect into their own operating model.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 text-center">API capability areas</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-center mb-12 leading-relaxed">
          The Cinturon360 API is being planned to support the full lifecycle of travel program management, giving TMCs and technology partners the integration flexibility they need.
        </p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
          {[
            { icon: '🏢', title: 'Client & Account Provisioning', description: 'Create and manage client accounts, organisational structures, and entity configurations programmatically.' },
            { icon: '👤', title: 'Traveller & Approver Management', description: 'Manage user profiles, roles, approval chains, and traveller data through structured API endpoints.' },
            { icon: '⚖️', title: 'Policy & Approval Workflows', description: 'Configure policy rules and approval paths, and trigger or process approval workflows via API.' },
            { icon: '✈️', title: 'Booking & Travel Data Exchange', description: 'Submit booking data from any channel and receive structured governance outputs in return.' },
            { icon: '📊', title: 'Reporting & Data Extraction', description: 'Pull spend, compliance, exception, and operational data into your own reporting and BI tools.' },
            { icon: '🔔', title: 'Webhooks & Event-Driven Workflows', description: 'Receive real-time events for approvals, policy outcomes, bookings, and audit activity.' },
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="card flex gap-4">
              <div class="text-2xl flex-shrink-0">{item.icon}</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">{item.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">{item.description}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <!-- Status notice -->
        <div class="bg-sky-50 border border-sky-200 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-sky-100 text-sky-700 mb-4">
            Pre-release
          </span>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">API documentation coming soon</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            The Cinturon360 API is currently in design and development. If you are a TMC, technology partner, or developer interested in integration discussions, get in touch.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
            <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Discuss Integration</a>
            <a href="/waitlist" class="btn-secondary">Join Waitlist</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTA />
</PageLayout>
